.TH HRC 1 "February 2026" "version 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hrc \- HTTP response code lookup tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hrc
.RB [ \-v ]
.I code
.br
.B hrc
.RB [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hrc
is a command-line tool for looking up HTTP response status codes. Given a numeric status code, it displays the standard status text and a detailed description including the relevant RFCs and usage context.
.PP
When invoked with a status code argument,
.B hrc
prints the information and exits. When invoked without arguments, it enters an interactive mode where you can look up multiple codes until you type 'q' to quit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode. Show extended details for each status code including common causes, real-world usage, related codes, troubleshooting tips, and RFC references.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B hrc 200
Look up the 200 OK status code
.TP
.B hrc 404
Look up the 404 Not Found status code
.TP
.B hrc 418
Look up the classic 418 I'm a teapot status code
.TP
.B hrc \-v 404
Look up the 404 Not Found status code with extended details
.TP
.B hrc
Enter interactive mode to look up multiple status codes
.TP
.B hrc \-v
Enter interactive mode with verbose output enabled
.SH SUPPORTED STATUS CODES
.SS 1xx Informational
100, 101, 102, 103
.SS 2xx Success
200, 201, 202, 203, 204, 205, 206, 207, 208, 226
.SS 3xx Redirection
300, 301, 302, 303, 304, 305, 306, 307, 308
.SS 4xx Client Error
400, 401, 402, 403, 404, 405, 406, 407, 408, 409, 410, 411, 412, 413, 414, 415, 416, 417, 418, 421, 422, 423, 424, 425, 426, 428, 429, 431, 451
.SS 5xx Server Error
500, 501, 502, 503, 504, 505, 506, 507, 508, 510, 511
.PP
Status codes recognized by Go's
.BR net/http
package but not in the built-in description table will display the standard status text without a detailed description.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.TP
.B Invalid code: \fISTRING\fR
The input was not a valid integer.
.TP
.B Unknown code: \fIN\fR
The integer is not a recognized HTTP status code.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR curl (1),
.BR http (1)
.PP
RFC 7231 (HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content), RFC 6585 (Additional HTTP Status Codes), RFC 7725 (451 Unavailable For Legal Reasons)
